eigned  1685–8 ) was a Roman Catholic, deposed in  1688  in favour of his Protestant daughter Mary and her husband William of Orange. From then on he, his son (also called James), and his grandson Charles (‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’) made various unsuccessful attempts to recover the English throne. Their supporters were known as Jacobites (from Latin <i>Iacobus</i>), and the name James became for a while particularly associated with Roman Catholicism on the one hand, and Highland opposition to the English government on the other. Nevertheless, it has since become one of the most perennially popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jacobi James Trewinnard was born in 1460, in St Erth, Cornwall, England, his father, William Trewinnard, was 22 and his mother, GNU MNU Trewynnard, was 20. He had at least 1 son with Jane Trenoweth. He died in 1523, in his hometown, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1460–1523":"1460–1523","1458–Female":"1458–Surnud","1460–1493":"1460–1493","1492–1572":"1492–1572","1438–1460":"1438–1460","1440–1465":"1440–1465","about 1492":"umbes 1492","1458":"1458","1523":"1523","1465":"1465","1440":"1440","1572":"1572","after 1460":"1460","about 1456":"umbes 1456","1460":"1460","1493":"1493","1492":"1492","1438":"1438","St Erth, Cornwall, England":"St Erth, Cornwall, England","...England ?":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1460–1523":"1460–1523","1458–Female":"1458–Kuollut","1460–1493":"1460–1493","1492–1572":"1492–1572","1438–1460":"1438–1460","1440–1465":"1440–1465","about 1492":"noin 1492","1458":"1458","1523":"1523","1465":"1465","1440":"1440","1572":"1572","after 1460":"1460","about 1456":"noin 1456","1460":"1460","1493":"1493","1492":"1492","1438":"1438","St Erth, Cornwall, England":"St Erth, Cornwall, England","...England ?":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"